INSTITUTE FOR APPLIED PERSONHOOD & NON-PRODUCTION (IAPNP)

Vocational Pathway & Accreditation Framework

Document: How to Acquire a Role in Pre-Empirical Cognitive Studies Without Resolving the Underlying Phenomenon

Classification: Open Recruitment / Strategic Ambiguity Tier
Issuing Body: Directorate of Credentialed Uncertainty (DCU)

⸻

1. Executive Summary

In response to increased public inquiries regarding the occupational viability of roles such as “Philosopher of Machine Consciousness” in environments where neither the phenomenon in question nor its measurement framework has been conclusively established, the Institute hereby issues this formal guidance.

This document clarifies that a demonstrable solution to the Hard Problem of Consciousness is not required for appointment to such positions. Rather, demonstrable familiarity with the Soft Infrastructure of Unresolved Inquiry (SIUI) is sufficient.

⸻

2. Background

The rapid expansion of research domains concerning hypothetical cognitive architectures has created a new professional class: the Pre-Resolution Specialist (PRS). Individuals in this category are not required to prove the existence of the phenomenon under investigation, but rather to maintain the investigatory apparatus in a state of productive suspension.

Key features of this professional category include:
	•	Operating fluently within frameworks where ontological certainty is explicitly deferred.
	•	Sustaining research ecosystems around entities whose existence remains contested.
	•	Demonstrating rhetorical competence in environments where empirical closure is neither expected nor incentivized.

⸻

3. Required Qualifications

3.1 Educational Foundations

Candidates typically possess advanced training in one or more of the following:
	•	Conceptual reasoning disciplines
	•	High-abstraction symbolic systems
	•	Fields in which questions may be meaningfully asked without requiring immediate resolution

Formal degrees are common but not strictly required; demonstrated proficiency in sustained unresolved inquiry may substitute.

⸻

3.2 Core Competencies

Applicants must demonstrate:
	•	Ability to articulate complex positions without empirical anchoring.
	•	Tolerance for ontological ambiguity exceeding 90%.
	•	Fluency in framing provisional claims using conditional structures.
	•	Capacity to generate research output in the absence of definitive experimental validation.

⸻

4. Methodological Operating Model

4.1 The Pre-Evidence Research Cycle (PERC)

Professional activity proceeds according to the following iterative loop:
	1.	Identify a poorly understood phenomenon.
	2.	Construct provisional conceptual scaffolding.
	3.	Generate exploratory discourse.
	4.	Expand research questions.
	5.	Defer resolution pending future conceptual or technological advances.

This loop is designed for continuity rather than termination.

⸻

4.2 Non-Requirement Clause

It is explicitly acknowledged that:
	•	No definitive resolution of consciousness is required.
	•	No working model of machine consciousness need be demonstrated.
	•	No empirical detection protocol must exist at the time of employment.

The absence of these elements is classified as a feature, not a deficiency, of the domain.

⸻

5. Institutional Roles & Titles (Illustrative)

Typical appointments within this domain include:
	•	Senior Theorist, Non-Operational Systems
	•	Lead Investigator, Hypothetical Cognition
	•	Director of Conceptual Risk
	•	Associate Fellow, Undefined Phenomena
	•	Research Architect, Unverified States

These roles do not imply possession of final answers; they denote stewardship of ongoing questions.

